ransport of the positrons over distances \\sim 1 kpc before\nannihilating. We note that an x-ray line of several keV in energy, due to\nsingle-photon decays involving the top DM states, could provide an additional\ncomponent to the diffuse x-ray background. The model is testable by proposed\nlow-energy fixed target experiments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Aug 2010 20:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 20 Aug 2010 02:11:47 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 17 Sep 2010 04:34:04 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 15 Aug 2011 18:04:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-08-16"}
